       <div>
        <h2>Let's bring the <i>thrill</i> back</h2>

        <p>Modern MMO's are too damn wimpy! The games play themselves and players are spoiled with eye candy like
         ginormous statues and breathtaking surroundings, from day one.</p>

        <p>
         But no more! I'm building <span class="title">We Ride</span> in an attempt to bring that <i>ultimate
          online</i> <abbr
           title="PLayer versus player">pvp</abbr> thrill back from the
         <abbr title="Role playing game">rpg</abbr>'s of the 90's.
        </p>

        <p>
         Also, I want it to be hard as hell.
         No magically flaming swords, no mighty castles. No, you live in a barren desert, you're gonna get killed and
         looted, and
         <b>you're gonna love it!</b>
        </p>

        <p><span class="btn scroll-btn">The basics</span></p>
       </div>
      </div>
